<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,474,969]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
A Palearctic species (see note below), all of whose known parasitic stages have been found on 
<taxonomicName box="[450,556,510,536]" class="Mammalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Rodentia</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[565,674,510,536]" class="Mammalia" family="Sciuridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Sciuridae</taxonomicName>
; immature stages have been collected from 
<taxonomicName box="[1159,1265,510,536]" class="Mammalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Rodentia</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[1274,1389,510,536]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Cricetidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,249,546,572]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Muridae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[259,397,546,572]" class="Aves" kingdom="Animalia" order="Galliformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Galliformes</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[407,544,546,572]" class="Aves" family="Phasianidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Galliformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Phasianidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[554,711,546,572]" class="Aves" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Passeriformes</taxonomicName>
(several families), and 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1099,546,572]" class="Aves" kingdom="Animalia" order="Piciformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Piciformes</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[1108,1194,546,572]" class="Aves" family="Picidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Piciformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Picidae</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takada and Fujita" authorityYear="1992" box="[1204,1392,546,572]" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Ixodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="columnae">
<emphasis box="[1204,1392,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Ixodes columnae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very rare parasite of humans.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
