<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,474,969]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,216,906,932]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Note:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Guglielmone, A. A. &amp; Robbins, R. G." box="[224,602,906,932]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref204760" refString="Guglielmone, A. A. &amp; Robbins, R. G. (2018) Hard ticks (Acari: Ixodida: Ixodidae) parasitizing humans. A global overview. Springer, Cham, 314 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 3 - 319 - 95552 - 0" type="book" year="2018">Guglielmone and Robbins (2018)</bibRefCitation>
state that if Taiwanese records in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuo, C. C. &amp; Lin, Y. F. &amp; Yao, C. T. &amp; Shih, H. C. &amp; Chung, L. H. &amp; Liao, H. C. &amp; Hsu, Y. C. &amp; Wang, H. C." box="[988,1184,906,933]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 1" refId="ref223315" refString="Kuo, C. C., Lin, Y. F., Yao, C. T., Shih, H. C., Chung, L. H., Liao, H. C., Hsu, Y. C. &amp; Wang, H. C. (2017) Tick-borne pathogens in ticks collected from birds in Taiwan. Parasites &amp; Vectors, 10 (article 587), 1 - 1. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / s 13071 - 017 - 2535 - 4" type="journal article" year="2017">
Kuo 
<emphasis box="[1044,1101,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
are confirmed, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takada and Fujita" authorityYear="1992" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Ixodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="columnae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Ixodes columnae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be an 
<collectingRegion box="[384,476,942,968]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Oriental</collectingRegion>
and Palearctic species.
</paragraph>
